						<summary>

						<p>On the east inner <hi rend="italic">gōpura,</hi> right of entrance, Svētāraṇyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 8: 979 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. It registers a gift of land (in Kūttaṅguḍi) probably after purchasing it for 25 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, for the maintenance of a perpetual lamp to the God, Tiruveṇkāḍu-dēvar, by [Mīna]van-Mahādēviyār, a queen of Uttamachōḷa. The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> undertook to burn the lamp.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX. No. 206.</p>						

						</summary>
